// Pseudo API Client
// HTTP fetch helpers for reading and searching .pseudo files via the backend REST API.
// synced: 2026-03-26T13:51:59Z

All functions use relative URLs against the same host. Errors are re-thrown to callers.

FUNCTION fetchPseudoFiles(project: string) -> Promise<string[]> [2026-03-26]                EXPORT
  GET /api/pseudo/files?project=<encoded>. Returns array of .pseudo filenames for the project.

---

FUNCTION fetchPseudoFile(project: string, file: string) -> Promise<string> [2026-03-26]     EXPORT
  GET /api/pseudo/file?project=<encoded>&file=<encoded>. Returns raw text content of one file.

---

FUNCTION fetchPseudoReferences(project, functionName, fileStem) -> Promise<Reference[]> [2026-03-26]  EXPORT
  GET /api/pseudo/references with URLSearchParams. Returns list of caller locations across files.

---

FUNCTION searchPseudo(project: string, q: string) -> Promise<SearchResult[]> [2026-03-26]   EXPORT
  GET /api/pseudo/search?project=<encoded>&q=<encoded>. Converts the matches map from the
  response into a flat array of SearchResult objects keyed by file path.
